nodes.text: A joyrider took a T-16 skyhopper to Agarees Shipyard Township. Corporal Jan Stakross later gave a warning to a group of individuals, particularly the joyrider, not to take the skyhopper to Agarees Shipyard Township anymore, since it came back infested with mynocks.

The joyrider was first mentioned in the "Mynock" entry in the in-game databank of the PlayStation 3/Xbox 360 versions of the LucasArts video game Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II, which was released on October 26, 2010.
